    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.16-17_0001"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">16</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        April 14, 1954
                        South Portland, Maine
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>c/o The Macmillan Co.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>New York.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am a Senior at the South Portland High School in South Portland, Maine. I am writing for my English class. We just finished reading your story of Hugh Glass and an argument arose as to Jamie's fate.</p>
                
                <p>We would like to know whether Jamie lived after Hugh found him or whether he died? Also we would like to know how long it took Hugh to find Jamie after Hugh left Henry's Post?</p>
                
                <p>We would be very grateful if you could take time to answer our questions. We are very much interested in these questions, and we have enjoyed
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.2316-17_0002"/>
                
                    reading this book.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Betty E. Crossman.</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.16-17_0003"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    Miss Betty <hi rend="caps">E.</hi> Crossman
                    126 Kelsey St
                    South Portland, Me
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    PORTLAND
                    APR 15
                    3 3<unclear/> PM
                    1954
                    MAINE

                    <hi rend="italics">Remember</hi> Only <hi rend="underline">you</hi> <unclear>can</unclear> <hi rend="caps">PREVENT FOREST FIRES</hi>
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITED STATES POSTAGE THOMAS JEFFERSON 1801-1809 3 CENTS 3</p>
                </figure>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">17</fw>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John G. Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>c/o The Macmillan Company</del></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>New York,</del></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>New York</del></addrLine>
                
                        <addrLine><add>Skyrim Farm</add></addrLine>
